  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN153.1-kilavi">makaṭpōkkiya <app><lem>cevili</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C7 #C9v #RK">ttāy</rdg></app> <app><lem>colliyatu</lem><rdg wit="#RK">coṟṟatu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the foster mother said who had let [her] daughter go.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN153.1">
              <l>nōkō yāṉē nōkku muḷḷa</l>
              <l>mantīṅ kiḷavi yāyamoṭu keḻīip</l>
              <l>pantuvaḻip paṭarkuva <supplied>ḷā</supplied>yiṉu nontunaṉi</l>
              <l>vempuma ṉaḷiya ṭāṉē yiṉiyē</l>
              <l>vaṉka ṇāḷaṉ mārpuṟa vaḷaii</l>
              <l>yiṉcoṟ piṇippa nampi <supplied>naṅka</supplied></l>
              <l>ṇuṟutaru viḻuma muḷḷā ḷoyyeṉat</l>
              <l>teṟu<supplied>ka</supplied>ti rulaiiya vēṉil veṅkāṭ</l>
              <l>ṭuṟuvaḷi yolikaḻai kaṇṇuṟu nīṇṭaliṟ</l>
              <l>poṟipitir peṭutta poṅkeḻu kūrerip</l>
              <l>paitaṟu cimaiyap payanīṅ kāriṭai</l>
              <l>nallaṭik kamainta valla melliyal</l>
              <l>vallu<supplied>na</supplied>ḷ kollō tāṉē <supplied>ye</supplied>lli</l>
              <l>yōṅkuvarai yaṭukat tuyarnta ceṉṉi</l>
              <l>mīṉoṭu polinta vāṉiṟ ṟōṉṟit</l>
              <l>tēmpāyn tārkkun teriyiṇar kōṅkiṉ</l>
              <l>kāluṟak kaḻaṉṟa taṇkamaḻ paṉimalar</l>
              <l>kaiviṭu cuṭariṟ ṟōṉṟu</l>
              <l>maipaṭu māmalai vilaṅkiya curaṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Ah, I ache in [my] heart that [still] looks [at her]: (1)</l>
                <l>Even if, together with [her] companions with pretty, sweet words, (2)</l>
                <l>she set out on the way with a ball, much aching (3)</l>
                <l>she would be hot indeed, pitiable she. Now, (4)</l>
                <l>encircling, so as to feel [it], the chest of a strong man, (5)</l>
                <l>trusting firmly in [his] sweet words she who does not think</l>
                <l>of the distress our eyes experience, in the hot wilderness</l>
                <l>in summer that harasses with searingly scorching rays, (6-8)</l>
                <l>with flickering, rising, sharp flames that scatter [and] raise sparks, (10)</l>
                <l>because the blowing wind extends [them] so as to get at the knots of the sprouting bamboo, (9)</l>
                <l>the long ways abandoned by fertility, with peaks devoid of green (11)</l>
                <l>are not suited to [her] fine feet. [She with] soft nature, (12)</l>
                <l>does she have the strength, she, at night, (13)</l>
                <l>– in the desert that is blocked by large mountains, touched by clouds, (19)</l>
                <l>where the peaks that are high above the flanks of the high mountains (14)</l>
                <l>appear like the sky that shines with stars (15)</l>
                <l>[and] the cool fragrant dewy blossoms that become loose when touched by the wind (17)</l>
                <l>of the cameg with clear [flower] clusters on which bees spread [and] hum (16)</l>
                <l>appear like fire set free? (18)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
